through the back.

76
00:04:42,573 --> 00:04:44,325
They won't make a lot operating legally.

77
00:04:45,451 --> 00:04:49,289
Once he's made enough money,
he'll take out a loan and buy a building.

78
00:04:49,372 --> 00:04:50,999
Then he'll use that as collateral

79
00:04:51,082 --> 00:04:53,668
for a bigger loan
and buy an even bigger building.

80
00:04:55,128 --> 00:04:56,713
That bastard is really something.

81
00:04:56,796 --> 00:05:00,258
He'll go harder running the casino
to pay back that loan.

82
00:05:00,341 --> 00:05:03,177
And Smile Capital will squeeze
even more people dry.

83
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:05,722
It'll be the opening
of Kim Myeong-gil's empire.

84
00:05:18,192 --> 00:05:23,781
Myeong-gil roughly stole
over 20 billion from me back then.

85
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:26,284
Once we get it back,

86
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:29,829
shall we go on a world trip
with Gun-woo and Woo-jin?

87
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:33,082
We have enough money as is.

88
00:05:35,084 --> 00:05:36,002
Yes,

89
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:38,963
but we can't go anywhere
because of COVID-19.

90
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:41,674
Well…

91
00:05:43,634 --> 00:05:44,635
Let's go to Rome.

92
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:48,556
Why Rome?

93
00:05:48,639 --> 00:05:52,226
When I was 20, I watched
a film called Roman Holiday.

94
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:56,356
I vowed to go someday
when I made a lot of money,

95
00:05:56,439 --> 00:05:57,857
but I haven't had the chance.

96
00:05:57,940 --> 00:06:01,611
I thought it might be nice
to go with you all,

97
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:03,863
the three of you.

98
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,827
I'll buy you guys anything you want.

99
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:14,040
Grandpa, there are
a lot of expensive things in Italy.

100
00:06:14,123 --> 00:06:15,541
It's the land of luxuries.

101
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:18,711
Hey, who do you think you're talking to?

102
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:21,672
I'll show you how it's done.

103
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:26,803
Grandpa, that's called "flex."

104
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:31,474
Yes, I'll show you how to "flex."

105
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:36,020
You don't show anything.
You just say "flex."

106
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:48,282
Right, let's all go together
once this is all finished.

107
00:07:04,757 --> 00:07:05,591
Yes, sir.

108
00:07:06,884 --> 00:07:08,302
Okay, that sounds good.

109
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:10,179
Yes, sir.

110
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:14,392
Mr. Choi invited us to come over
for drinks at his place.

111
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:18,020
I guess he's in a good mood.

112
00:07:19,605 --> 00:07:20,773
Do you guys drink?

113
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:22,775
We'd love to go!

114
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:19,457
Can you speed it up?

115
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:21,834
Do you want double or quadruple-speed?

116
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:23,252
-Let's do double.
-Okay.

117
00:08:30,092 --> 00:08:32,053
If I were Kim Myeong-gil,

118
00:08:32,136 --> 00:08:35,681
I would've moved the hard drive
to a safer location,

119
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:38,434
assuming that Im Jang-do revealed
all of his weaknesses.

120
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:41,771
Do you think he's able to pull that off?

121
00:08:41,854 --> 00:08:44,899
We've tied down
Kim Myeong-gil's arms and legs.

122
00:08:44,982 --> 00:08:48,528
He has no one left to mobilize
except for Jung now.

123
00:08:49,362 --> 00:08:50,238
Besides,

124
00:08:51,155 --> 00:08:54,116
I don't think Kim would entrust
just anyone with that information.

125
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:56,911
He doesn't have to move it far.

126
00:08:57,411 --> 00:08:59,413
If he hid it in the trunk,
we wouldn't know.

127
00:09:00,164 --> 00:09:01,541
Kim Myeong-gil knows that.

128
00:09:02,291 --> 00:09:03,251
You're right.

129
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:07,255
If we were to recruit
an enemy of his over to our side,

130
00:09:07,338 --> 00:09:09,215
the tides would turn in our favor.

131
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:13,970
But in order to do that,
we need the hard drive.

132
00:09:14,053 --> 00:09:17,598
It should contain a lot of information
on Myeong-gil's blackmail victims.

133
00:09:18,099 --> 00:09:20,643
Those people have the same motive as us.

134
00:09:22,019 --> 00:09:26,399
There will be many powerful people,
like the Iil Group heir.

135
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:31,821
The longer this fight goes on,
the more were at a disadvantage.

136
00:09:32,488 --> 00:09:35,741
I'm sure Myeong-gil has made
a vast network of connections by now.

137
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:39,996
He will have every cop, prosecutor,
and politician that could be bought off

138
00:09:40,746 --> 00:09:42,039
in his pocket by now.

139
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:45,668
If we let our guard down
for even a moment, we'll lose our edge.

140
00:09:46,627 --> 00:09:47,545
Right.

141
00:09:47,628 --> 00:09:51,173
But it's true we took down
three of his cronies, right?

142
00:09:51,882 --> 00:09:52,717
Yes.

143
00:09:53,718 --> 00:09:56,262
You're bound to get anxious
if you think too far ahead.

144
00:09:56,887 --> 00:09:59,599
The way I see it,
I think we're all doing pretty well.

145
00:09:59,682 --> 00:10:01,225
No one's gotten hurt so far.

146
00:10:01,892 --> 00:10:02,727
That's right.

147
00:10:03,561 --> 00:10:05,271
Let's take things one at a time.

148
00:10:05,354 --> 00:10:08,274
We can take Kim Myeong-gil down,
then his company.

149
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:12,194
Besides, now that Im Jang-do
and Kim Jun-min are gone,

150
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:14,530
Kim Myeong-gil probably got
a reality check.

151
00:10:17,158 --> 00:10:18,951
I guess you have a point.

152
00:10:20,828 --> 00:10:22,163
Well…

153
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,792
Right.

154
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:28,461
Mr. Choi. Dear seniors.

155
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:36,135
I would like to propose a toast
for our safety and our shared goal.

156
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:40,014
When I lead with,
"Let's find that hard drive,"

157
00:10:40,097 --> 00:10:45,186
please follow up with,
"Kim Myeong-gil is done for."

158
00:10:45,269 --> 00:10:47,355
Let's get started.
Please raise your glasses.

159
00:10:49,398 --> 00:10:51,692
Let's find that hard drive.
Kim Myeong-gil is…

160
00:10:51,776 --> 00:10:53,694
-Done for!
-Done for!

161
00:11:44,787 --> 00:11:46,539
Yes, I'm going to Joongang Station.

162
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:49,291
Those bastards went
from Dongpa-gu to Joongang-gu.

163
00:11:50,084 --> 00:11:51,836
Can you find them by 3:00 p.m.?

164
00:11:52,837 --> 00:11:54,797
I can if they stopped in Joongang-gu,

165
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:57,007
but if they crossed over
to another district,

166
00:11:57,091 --> 00:11:58,551
I'll have to keep looking.

167
00:12:00,344 --> 00:12:01,512
Please help me.

168
00:12:01,595 --> 00:12:03,097
Don't worry about it.

169
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:05,725
We'll do what the bastard wants for now.

170
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:09,979
Once it's done, I'll think of a way
to fuck this guy up.

171
00:12:10,855 --> 00:12:11,731
Thank you.

172
00:12:12,314 --> 00:12:16,527
Min-beom, you think I'd leave some bastard
messing with my family alone?

173
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:18,404
Don't worry.

174
00:12:18,487 --> 00:12:19,572
Okay?

175
00:12:19,655 --> 00:12:21,198
You're all I have.

176
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:24,243
Don't drink too much, okay?

177
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:25,786
Okay.

178
00:12:46,515 --> 00:12:49,226
Gosh. Why did he drink so much
if he's such a lightweight?

179
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:50,352
I guess

180
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:52,772
he was in a good mood today.

181
00:12:52,855 --> 00:12:54,815
I'm sleepy. What about you?

182
00:12:54,899 --> 00:12:56,400
I'm heading back downstairs.

183
00:12:56,484 --> 00:12:58,235
-Aren't you tired?
-Yes, I'm fine.

184
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:02,782
Good work today.

185
00:13:02,865 --> 00:13:03,824
Sure.

186
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:10,956
Gun-woo.

187
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:13,292
Gun-woo.

188
00:13:15,336 --> 00:13:16,253
Mom, aren't you asleep?

189
00:13:17,546 --> 00:13:18,923
No, why are you awake?

190
00:13:19,006 --> 00:13:21,008
I'm having a drink
with everyone downstairs.

191
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:23,928
-You're drinking too?
-No, of course not.

192
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:24,887
Goodness.

193
00:13:26,722 --> 00:13:28,933
I'll make hangover soup in the morning.

194
00:13:29,016 --> 00:13:30,935
Okay. Get some sleep. I'll close the door.

195
00:13:31,018 --> 00:13:32,561
Okay, sleep tight.

196
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:33,813
Good night.

197
00:13:36,106 --> 00:13:38,859
It's nice drinking with you
after such a long time.

198
00:13:58,337 --> 00:13:59,171
Is it a woman?

199
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:00,631
Yes.

200
00:14:01,131 --> 00:14:02,842
Who would call you at this hour?

201
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:08,556
Tell me.

202
00:14:10,766 --> 00:14:11,600
Yang-jung.

203
00:14:14,478 --> 00:14:15,688
I'm going to be a dad.

204
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:18,524
